>, <i>Cornall</i>, <i>Gorney</i>, and <i>Gornall</i>.","perhaps a shortened form of   Cornwall   or   Cornish  , or a metathesized form of   Croney  .","English:"]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Gorball was born in 1520, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Bridgett Null +. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"1520–":"1520–Surnud","1525–1612":"1525–1612","1550–1615":"1550–1615","1520–Male":"1520–Surnud","1525":"1525","1612":"1612","1520":"1520","1550":"1550","1615":"1615","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1520–":"1520–Kuollut","1525–1612":"1525–1612","1550–1615":"1550–1615","1520–Male":"1520–Kuollut","1525":"1525","1612":"1612","1520":"1520","1550":"1550","1615":"1615","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1520–":"1520–Décédé","1525–1612":"1525–1612","1550–1615":"1550–1615","1520–Male":"1520–Décédé","1525":"1525","1612":"1612","1520":"1520","1550":"1550","1615":"1615","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Gorball est né en 1520, à Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Bridgett Null +. Il est décédé dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1520–":"1520–Verstorben","1525–1612